WEBVTT

00:05.106 --> 00:06.707
This won't be the first time
I've had to be glamorous

00:07.007 --> 00:08.242
under my husband.

00:08.776 --> 00:11.679
<i>I decided long ago
that I will say how I feel.</i>

00:11.712 --> 00:13.047
Well, if you're gonna put me on the stand,

00:13.080 --> 00:14.448
I better have my lawyer present.

00:14.482 --> 00:16.650
<i>The election
is in eight fucking months.</i>

00:16.684 --> 00:19.453
<i>Keep your mouth shut, we'll be fine.</i>

00:19.487 --> 00:22.156
Get another wife if you want a silent one.

00:23.124 --> 00:24.425
They used to like each other.

00:24.458 --> 00:27.094
<i>You're a good person deep down.</i>

00:28.662 --> 00:31.031
<i>Met a young couple
tonight reminded me of being</i>

00:31.065 --> 00:33.033
at the beginning of something.

00:33.067 --> 00:34.502
McCord, wasn't it?

00:34.535 --> 00:36.303
I appreciate you, James McCord.

00:37.171 --> 00:38.606
California?

00:38.639 --> 00:40.274
<i>We got a couple
of fundraisers out there.</i>

00:40.307 --> 00:43.177
- My mom says Nixon's dogshit.
- I've never even met the guy.

00:43.210 --> 00:45.746
We got a kind of
special opportunity for you.

00:45.780 --> 00:47.581
You mean you want to set up
an espionage unit

00:47.615 --> 00:50.217
<i>here, in- inside the Committee
to Re-elect.</i>

00:50.251 --> 00:51.051
I think I know a guy.

00:51.085 --> 00:53.654
- Liddy, general counsel.
- Soldier.

00:53.687 --> 00:55.689
<i>This operation requires</i>

00:55.723 --> 00:58.092
<i>untraceable foreign contractors.</i>

00:58.125 --> 00:59.393
I need five Cubans.

00:59.427 --> 01:01.562
How expensive are Cubans these days?

01:01.595 --> 01:05.299
<i>They're freedom
fighters, you fuck!</i>

01:09.503 --> 01:11.305
- <i>Mr. Dean?</i>
- <i>I'll see myself out.</i>

01:11.338 --> 01:13.674
There she is, <i>machos...</i>

01:13.707 --> 01:15.209
our destiny.

01:15.242 --> 01:16.343
<i>El Watergate.</i>

01:54.348 --> 01:56.116
Voilà, Mrs. Mitchell.

01:57.518 --> 01:58.519
What do you think?

02:00.187 --> 02:02.490
I don't-I don't see a difference.

02:02.523 --> 02:03.557
We love it.

02:03.591 --> 02:05.259
I knew you would.

02:11.298 --> 02:13.234
I'm noticing a few gaps

02:13.267 --> 02:15.236
in your employment history.

02:15.803 --> 02:18.305
One here in 1965,

02:18.339 --> 02:22.343
and here a whole year in 1969.

02:22.376 --> 02:24.178
You mind explaining what you were doing

02:24.211 --> 02:26.180
during those periods?

02:26.213 --> 02:29.683
I guess you could say
there was times I was doing it

02:29.717 --> 02:34.722
and, um, you know,
times I was getting it done.

02:34.755 --> 02:36.323
You know what I mean, brother?

02:38.559 --> 02:40.694
I'm afraid I do not.

02:40.728 --> 02:42.429
Mm-hmm.

02:43.464 --> 02:46.934
Um, just odd jobs, mostly.

02:48.202 --> 02:49.403
Mr. Wills--

02:49.436 --> 02:52.573
Frank, you can just--
you just call me Frank.

02:52.606 --> 02:56.210
Mr. Wills, I really appreciate, um,

02:56.243 --> 02:57.811
you coming all the way down here,

02:57.845 --> 03:01.916
but I'm afraid you're not
what we're looking for.

03:01.949 --> 03:03.918
What- what is it?
My-my mustache?

03:03.951 --> 03:05.719
'Cause I can shave it off, no problem.

03:05.753 --> 03:07.254
To be honest,

03:07.288 --> 03:09.690
you're not really a right fit
for the front desk.

03:09.723 --> 03:11.725
Come on, man, please.

03:11.759 --> 03:13.360
Look, I'll level with you.

03:13.394 --> 03:16.830
I've been to, like, ten
of these interviews this week.

03:16.864 --> 03:19.266
I got my bills up to here.

03:19.300 --> 03:21.869
If this ain't working for me,

03:21.902 --> 03:24.238
I'm out of this town, dig?

03:24.271 --> 03:27.241
Now, you just tell me, what do I gotta do?

03:32.580 --> 03:34.348
Name the capitals.

03:36.417 --> 03:37.685
Sorry?

03:37.718 --> 03:40.721
If you're on the front desk,
you only have one job,

03:40.754 --> 03:45.392
and that job is to make
white folks feel secure,

03:45.426 --> 03:49.396
<i>and nothing makes white folks
feel more secure</i>

03:49.430 --> 03:53.300
than a friendly public-school-educated boy

03:53.334 --> 03:55.502
<i>that knows the capitals.</i>

03:56.570 --> 03:59.873
Now, if you feel that's unfair,

03:59.907 --> 04:01.508
I hear that the Howard Johnson's

04:01.542 --> 04:03.277
across the street is hiring.

04:05.312 --> 04:06.847
What you want?

04:09.950 --> 04:12.319
Yeah, I got the job.

04:12.353 --> 04:14.455
The night job at the Watergate.

04:14.488 --> 04:16.457
Yeah, guy hired me on a provisional basis,

04:16.490 --> 04:18.993
but that's only 'cause I forgot Bismarck.

04:19.026 --> 04:20.561
It's the capital of North Dakota.

04:20.594 --> 04:21.862
Look, never mind. The bus is coming.

04:21.895 --> 04:23.664
I will tell you about it later.

04:23.697 --> 04:26.767
All right, I gotta go.
All right, all right, bye.

04:26.800 --> 04:29.436
Oh, I-I'm so sorry, man.

04:31.405 --> 04:34.608
We're all flaked with sorrow
from birth, son.

04:34.642 --> 04:36.810
It's up to each of us to pull it off.

04:38.445 --> 04:39.880
No apology necessary.

05:10.944 --> 05:12.312
Shh.

05:20.421 --> 05:21.989
Eagle.

05:22.022 --> 05:23.557
Falcon.

05:43.010 --> 05:46.113
The whole point
of breaking into the DNC

05:46.346 --> 05:49.550
was to capture intimate
campaign conversations.

05:50.884 --> 05:53.721
And you idiots, you bug
the secretarial lines?

05:56.490 --> 05:59.993
Hey, Gordo. What's up, compadre?

06:00.027 --> 06:02.029
All these transcripts, Howard.

06:02.062 --> 06:03.030
Uh-huh.

06:03.063 --> 06:04.965
We've got nothing

06:04.998 --> 06:07.668
but a secretary
dirty-birding her boyfriend.

06:09.002 --> 06:12.106
"I am in my posy-pink panties.

06:12.139 --> 06:14.675
"They're so cute

06:14.708 --> 06:16.944
stretched across my little red bottom."

06:16.977 --> 06:20.614
Jesus, I wish I could get
my wife to talk like that.

06:21.949 --> 06:23.150
You have any idea

06:23.383 --> 06:24.985
how this reflects on the two of us, Hunt?

06:25.018 --> 06:27.054
This operation? To Mitchell and everybody?

06:27.087 --> 06:28.722
Yeah.

06:28.756 --> 06:31.625
Now, I want to know

06:31.658 --> 06:35.462
which one of you slack-jawed
equines placed these taps.

06:36.764 --> 06:38.665
Hmm? Who was it?

06:43.670 --> 06:45.806
- Look--
- Oh, we have a winner.

06:45.839 --> 06:47.074
I can't stop a secretary

06:47.107 --> 06:49.009
from using the phone for personal calls.

06:49.042 --> 06:51.044
You bug the source, not the ancillary.

06:51.078 --> 06:52.579
Are you familiar with black bag ops?

06:52.613 --> 06:54.047
- You've done black bag ops.
- You ever done that?

06:54.081 --> 06:56.817
Honestly, maybe it'd be better
to find another target.

06:57.885 --> 07:00.120
Hold on. I'm sorry.

07:00.154 --> 07:03.490
Are you the target finder now?

07:03.524 --> 07:07.561
Are-are you the main guy
who helps us find the targets?

07:07.594 --> 07:10.831
Nixon's beating the hell
out of McGovern in every poll.

07:10.864 --> 07:13.167
Is the DNC really his biggest threat?

07:13.200 --> 07:17.104
It is not your job
to determine the threat level,

07:17.137 --> 07:18.205
you dumb donkey.

07:18.438 --> 07:19.573
It's your job to sit by the phone

07:19.606 --> 07:21.975
and wait for a fucking order.

07:22.009 --> 07:25.612
Now, do you think you can do your job?

07:26.446 --> 07:28.649
Insofar as any of this is my job?

07:29.616 --> 07:31.151
Yes, sir. I can do my job.

07:31.185 --> 07:32.186
Brilliant.

07:35.489 --> 07:37.624
Okay.

07:37.658 --> 07:39.760
We gotta go in again.

07:39.793 --> 07:40.894
It's our only option.

07:40.928 --> 07:42.095
Yeah, somebody's gonna have

07:42.129 --> 07:44.131
to ask Mitchell for more money.

07:44.164 --> 07:45.699
I can do it.

07:45.732 --> 07:48.669
You're going to get more
out of Mitchell if you send me

07:48.702 --> 07:49.903
rather than one of the wetbacks.

07:49.937 --> 07:51.538
- No offense.
- <i>Oye, coño.</i>

07:51.572 --> 07:52.539
Who you calling a wetback, brother?

07:52.573 --> 07:53.807
We're Cuban, not Mexican.

07:53.841 --> 07:55.209
<i>Okay, okay, take it easy.</i>

07:55.242 --> 07:57.611
I'll do it.

07:57.644 --> 07:59.179
But I'm gonna need a lift.

07:59.213 --> 08:02.049
Sarah's got the station wagon today.

08:06.620 --> 08:07.688
Of course.

08:10.591 --> 08:13.093
- <i>After you.</i>
- You guys are so sensitive.

08:17.197 --> 08:18.198
[Martinez, in Spanish] <i>I don't get it.</i>

08:18.232 --> 08:20.934
They look like amateurs, so weird.

08:20.968 --> 08:22.669
Look,

08:22.703 --> 08:25.572
if Nixon doesn't get elected,

08:25.606 --> 08:27.608
we'll never get Fidel out of Cuba.

08:27.641 --> 08:30.844
It's true. Let's remember why
we are doing this--

08:30.878 --> 08:36.216
For Cuba.

08:38.752 --> 08:41.622
This guy doesn't stop eating.

08:43.790 --> 08:47.227
<i>You're listening to WRBT...</i>

08:47.261 --> 08:48.929
<i>No, oh, no, honey, honey.</i>

08:48.962 --> 08:50.731
If you're gonna bring more
than three pairs of shoes,

08:50.764 --> 08:51.832
you gotta do it in secret,

08:51.865 --> 08:53.233
or else people lose faith in you.

08:54.635 --> 08:56.203
You don't do anything in secret.

08:58.939 --> 09:00.874
- Mr. McCord.
- Hello.

09:00.908 --> 09:02.609
- How are you?
- Fine, thank you.

09:05.312 --> 09:06.780
What can I do for you?

09:06.813 --> 09:08.548
Uh, I'm just here to drop off

09:08.582 --> 09:10.550
some papers for your husband.

09:10.584 --> 09:11.652
Oh, sure.

09:11.685 --> 09:13.720
Um, Marty, Katarina, would you--

09:13.754 --> 09:14.855
could you find Mr. Mitchell, please?

09:14.888 --> 09:16.156
He's around here somewhere.

09:16.189 --> 09:17.724
Sorry to bother you at home.

09:17.758 --> 09:19.126
I tried his office first.

09:20.761 --> 09:22.829
I was sorry to hear

09:22.863 --> 09:25.599
that you were taken off my detail.

09:25.632 --> 09:26.733
Apologies.

09:26.767 --> 09:27.968
I wanted to tell you myself,

09:28.001 --> 09:29.670
but it all happened so quickly.

09:29.703 --> 09:31.905
They put me on some security work.

09:31.939 --> 09:34.908
Clerical stuff mostly.

09:34.942 --> 09:38.679
Oh, this is a fine collection.

09:38.712 --> 09:40.247
You like it?

09:40.280 --> 09:43.784
Mm, I don't know if you
can say you like Rilke.

09:44.685 --> 09:49.289
There's so much desire
in there and... isolation.

09:50.190 --> 09:51.658
I don't know.

09:51.692 --> 09:53.360
I had to turn 40 before I got any of it.

09:53.593 --> 09:55.629
Oh, well, I'll give it a try
in a few years, then.

09:59.032 --> 10:03.170
Um, Mr. McCord, uh, my-my family and I,

10:03.203 --> 10:05.939
we are traveling out
to California for a fundraiser.

10:05.973 --> 10:09.009
I was wondering if you would
like to accompany us there.

10:10.077 --> 10:14.014
Oh, I would love to, Mrs. Mitchell, but...

10:14.047 --> 10:16.316
the campaign does have me very busy,

10:16.350 --> 10:19.820
and, um, I am needed at home.

10:19.853 --> 10:21.021
Of course, understood.

10:21.054 --> 10:24.224
I just--um, I don't often find a bodyguard

10:24.257 --> 10:26.793
that I can have a conversation
with, that's all.

10:26.827 --> 10:29.096
I'm sorry if I overstepped.

10:29.129 --> 10:32.199
Oh, no, no, no, no. Of course not.

10:32.232 --> 10:34.034
McCord?

10:34.067 --> 10:35.102
Yes, sir.

10:35.135 --> 10:36.970
Uh, I have a few matters of paperwork

10:37.004 --> 10:39.306
pertaining to our earlier conversation.

10:40.207 --> 10:41.875
In the study.

10:46.380 --> 10:47.848
It's very nice to see you again.

10:47.881 --> 10:48.882
Oh.

11:02.863 --> 11:04.197
<i>What are you doing with my book?</i>

11:05.999 --> 11:08.201
Helping you not forget it.

11:23.150 --> 11:24.985
Is he, um--

11:25.018 --> 11:26.720
you think he'll be out soon?

11:26.753 --> 11:28.055
I-I don't mean to be rude.

11:28.088 --> 11:30.290
It's just, I ha-I have a plane
to catch this afternoon

11:30.323 --> 11:32.059
for a conference in the Philippines.

11:32.092 --> 11:33.460
The president should be wrapping up

11:33.693 --> 11:36.196
with Senator Thurmond in just a moment.

11:36.229 --> 11:37.364
Hard candy?

11:40.734 --> 11:42.936
Couple of Chatty Cathys.

11:42.969 --> 11:45.872
It shouldn't be
too much longer. Mr. Keane.

11:49.176 --> 11:51.011
- Dean.
- I'm sorry?

11:51.044 --> 11:53.947
My last name. You just called me Keane.

11:53.980 --> 11:55.248
- Keane?
- Dean.

11:55.282 --> 11:57.050
- With a K?
- With a D.

11:58.285 --> 11:59.786
Dean.

11:59.820 --> 12:00.987
I don't remember a Dean

12:01.021 --> 12:03.190
in the Department of Transportation.

12:04.091 --> 12:05.292
Excuse me?

12:05.325 --> 12:06.793
<i>You're an assistant secretary</i>

12:06.827 --> 12:09.296
in the Department of Transportation?

12:10.464 --> 12:12.299
N-no. What?

12:12.332 --> 12:13.733
I'm junior counsel.

12:13.767 --> 12:15.402
Oh, gosh.

12:15.435 --> 12:18.805
What is my brain doing up there?

12:23.410 --> 12:25.011
Yes, Mr. President?

12:25.979 --> 12:30.350
<i>Um, Mr. Dean has been here
for the past 45 minutes.</i>

12:32.085 --> 12:34.321
Uh-huh. Certainly, I'll let him know.

12:34.354 --> 12:35.755
Thank you, Mr. President.

12:37.457 --> 12:39.092
<i>The president apologizes,</i>

12:39.126 --> 12:41.027
<i>but his meeting with Senator Thurmond</i>

12:41.061 --> 12:44.064
<i>has been extended indefinitely.</i>

12:44.097 --> 12:46.399
Fortunately, it looks
like we can reschedule

12:46.433 --> 12:48.835
your get-to-know-you for September.

12:49.936 --> 12:50.904
September?

12:53.073 --> 12:54.341
It's June.

12:54.374 --> 12:55.809
That's the next space

12:55.842 --> 12:57.310
the president has available,

12:57.344 --> 12:59.012
unless that's a problem.

13:05.852 --> 13:07.354
I serve at the pleasure of the president.

13:07.387 --> 13:09.422
That's the spirit.

13:13.793 --> 13:16.029
President Fucking Dick.

13:16.062 --> 13:18.331
Fucking piece of fucking asshole.

13:18.365 --> 13:20.433
Fucking, fucking shit. Fuck.

13:24.337 --> 13:25.972
Ow, Jesus.

13:26.006 --> 13:28.008
<i>Sir, I have
Maureen Kane returning.</i>

13:29.576 --> 13:31.378
Miss Kane.

13:31.411 --> 13:34.080
Hi. Well, I--God, that's all

13:34.114 --> 13:35.982
a girl's gotta do to reach
White House counsel?

13:36.016 --> 13:39.419
I think I imagined switchboards
all the way up Mount Olympus.

13:39.452 --> 13:41.321
Stop, I'm not that important.

13:41.354 --> 13:43.823
<i>Oh, Mr. False Modesty.</i>

13:43.857 --> 13:45.058
So come on, you have to tell me.

13:45.091 --> 13:46.459
How'd it go, anyway?

13:46.493 --> 13:48.094
<i>How- how'd what go?</i>

13:48.128 --> 13:51.331
Your meeting with the president
of the United States?

13:51.364 --> 13:53.500
Oh, that, I--yeah, I, um--

13:53.533 --> 13:56.903
<i>No, I-I-I had to reschedule
that, actually.</i>

13:56.937 --> 13:58.471
You had to reschedule?

13:58.505 --> 14:00.574
Yeah, you know, I-I've been so busy lately

14:00.607 --> 14:02.309
with, uh, you know, meetings and stuff.

14:02.342 --> 14:03.577
You don't think that's rude, do you,

14:03.610 --> 14:05.011
to reschedule a meeting
with the president?

14:05.045 --> 14:06.947
Maybe it looks like I'm too busy for him.

14:06.980 --> 14:09.849
Uh, no, I-I don't--
I think it's a good thing,

14:09.883 --> 14:12.385
shows you're not sitting around
like the village idiot

14:12.419 --> 14:13.920
<i>waiting for him to meet with you.</i>

14:13.954 --> 14:16.122
<i>You've, you know,
got other things going on.</i>

14:16.156 --> 14:17.991
<i>- Important things.</i>
- Right.

14:18.024 --> 14:19.559
Blonde, important,

14:19.593 --> 14:21.861
"best thing that ever happened
to you" things.

14:21.895 --> 14:23.630
Well, that reminds me,
I-I got some bad news.

14:23.863 --> 14:25.899
I-I don't think I can make it
to see you this weekend.

14:27.901 --> 14:28.969
What? No.

14:29.002 --> 14:30.537
I've got the tickets to Cat Stevens

14:30.570 --> 14:32.038
at the Bowl Saturday night.

14:32.072 --> 14:33.873
<i>I know, and I love Cat Stevens,</i>

14:33.907 --> 14:35.575
but I have this conference in Manila.

14:35.609 --> 14:37.510
It totally slipped my mind. I'm sorry.

14:40.080 --> 14:41.381
I have Senator Gurney on the line,

14:41.414 --> 14:43.116
and he says it's urgent.

14:43.149 --> 14:44.317
Right.

14:44.351 --> 14:47.120
Look, I-I gotta take
this other call, but, um,

14:47.153 --> 14:48.221
on my way back through the States,

14:48.255 --> 14:49.422
how about I stop by LA?

14:49.456 --> 14:52.492
<i>Who's playing at the Bowl Tuesday?</i>

14:52.525 --> 14:55.495
- The Mormon Tabernacle Choir.
- Perfect.

14:55.528 --> 14:56.663
I love--it's beautiful. I--

14:56.896 --> 14:58.164
We'll make a night of it, okay?

14:58.198 --> 14:59.299
<i>I'll talk to you soon.</i>

15:01.167 --> 15:03.103
Okay, I'll light a candle in my window.

15:03.136 --> 15:04.404
Bye, now.

15:21.054 --> 15:22.522
Anything else, Mrs. Mitchell?

15:22.555 --> 15:24.291
I'm fine. Thank you, dear.

15:24.324 --> 15:26.159
Oh, and about your daughter.

15:26.192 --> 15:28.128
She asked for a Bloody Mary.

15:28.161 --> 15:29.663
Okay.

15:29.696 --> 15:31.031
She's 11 years old, ma'am.

15:31.064 --> 15:32.932
Mm-hmm. Oh, I see.

15:32.966 --> 15:34.200
Don't make it too spicy.

15:36.636 --> 15:38.972
Three campaign events in one day,

15:39.005 --> 15:41.541
we'll die of dumbfuck exposure.

15:45.979 --> 15:47.614
<i>You reading poetry now?</i>

15:50.717 --> 15:52.986
I'm in a bit
of a wistful mood, I guess,

15:53.019 --> 15:56.256
thinking about a... a boy I once knew.

15:58.558 --> 16:01.161
Is this gonna be the
center fielder from college?

16:02.495 --> 16:04.531
<i>The oil baron from Midland?</i>

16:05.699 --> 16:07.967
Walter. Arkansas boy.

16:08.001 --> 16:10.136
Took me to my first dance when we were 12.

16:10.170 --> 16:11.137
<i>Mm.</i>

16:12.305 --> 16:14.240
And once in a while,

16:14.274 --> 16:16.443
you still wonder
what it might have been like

16:16.476 --> 16:19.312
if you had married
simple Walter from Pine Bluff.

16:26.353 --> 16:28.154
We used to be a team.

16:30.690 --> 16:32.192
Now it's just...

16:35.628 --> 16:37.364
...jokes and silences

16:37.397 --> 16:41.501
and the occasional rough sex
and campaign business.

16:41.534 --> 16:43.236
Doesn't sound so bad.

16:43.269 --> 16:44.504
I'm serious.

16:44.537 --> 16:46.473
I thought you'd be happy
going to California.

16:46.506 --> 16:48.575
You can talk to Zsa Zsa and Clint.

16:48.608 --> 16:50.643
Push Lana Turner in the pool.

16:50.677 --> 16:52.145
I'm not a show pony.

16:52.178 --> 16:53.780
You can't just trot me around
and then put me back

16:54.013 --> 16:55.782
in the stable at the end of the night.

16:56.015 --> 16:58.017
<i>I don't know
what you want me to say.</i>

16:58.051 --> 16:59.552
These things happen in a marriage,

16:59.586 --> 17:02.021
and you didn't marry
simple Walter from Pine Bluff.

17:02.055 --> 17:03.423
You married me.

17:19.506 --> 17:21.408
I like your traveling suit.

17:28.715 --> 17:30.583
Ten Americans killed,

17:30.617 --> 17:33.253
eight missing, 75 wounded.

