17:37.390 --> 17:40.827
<i>the heaviest weekly toll
for them for the entire war.</i>

17:41.060 --> 17:44.597
Gotta get the crease right.

17:44.631 --> 17:47.300
<i>President Nixon
said last night...</i>

17:47.333 --> 17:49.736
See that?

17:49.769 --> 17:52.572
It's all in the details, Tuffy.

17:52.605 --> 17:54.574
Look at you licking the plate.

18:01.414 --> 18:03.183
I will be back at the crack of dawn,

18:03.216 --> 18:05.084
and I'm bringing doughnuts.

18:08.521 --> 18:12.158
I'm all right. Thank you, thank you.

18:12.192 --> 18:13.359
Ma'am.

18:13.393 --> 18:15.195
How you doing this evening?

18:17.464 --> 18:18.865
All right.

18:21.568 --> 18:23.136
Oh, man, don't mind Mrs. Emerson.

18:23.169 --> 18:24.571
She's, um--

18:24.604 --> 18:25.805
she's a little skittish.

18:25.839 --> 18:27.373
<i>Name's Alberto.</i>

18:27.407 --> 18:29.709
- Frank Wills.
- Nice to meet you.

18:29.742 --> 18:30.877
Yeah.

18:31.110 --> 18:32.645
You ever work security before,
Frank Wills?

18:32.679 --> 18:35.248
Well, I, um--I was up
in Michigan at Job Corps...

18:35.281 --> 18:36.349
- Mm-hmm.
- ...and before that,

18:36.382 --> 18:38.117
I was working part-time

18:38.151 --> 18:40.119
at a department store back in Georgia.

18:40.153 --> 18:43.756
Well, things around here
are pretty simple.

18:43.790 --> 18:45.592
Uh, there's the logbook,

18:45.625 --> 18:48.561
schedule, uh, walkie,

18:48.595 --> 18:50.263
flashlight for your rounds.

18:50.296 --> 18:52.699
Anyone comes down for a package,

18:52.732 --> 18:54.501
we keep them under the desk.

18:56.503 --> 18:59.138
Shit, man, uh, weekend's a dead zone.

18:59.172 --> 19:00.874
Oh, there's a bum who comes around

19:00.907 --> 19:04.477
and pisses in the planters,
but that's about it.

19:04.511 --> 19:05.845
I got you.

19:06.746 --> 19:08.481
Have a good night.

19:08.515 --> 19:11.217
And hey, don't fall asleep on the job.

19:11.251 --> 19:12.852
Got it.

19:12.886 --> 19:14.487
At least don't get caught.

19:25.532 --> 19:27.534
Eagle Eye, this is Sparrow.

19:27.567 --> 19:28.668
Come in, Eagle Eye.

19:29.536 --> 19:32.171
<i>Go for Eagle Eye. Over.</i>

19:32.205 --> 19:34.240
The guards have just
changed shifts for the night.

19:34.274 --> 19:35.742
Over.

19:35.775 --> 19:37.477
<i>How are we doing otherwise? Over.</i>

19:41.414 --> 19:43.650
<i>We still have
a few guys in the office.</i>

19:43.683 --> 19:46.853
<i>Looks like they're packing up
to get out of there. Over.</i>

19:46.886 --> 19:48.388
<i>Copy that.</i>

19:48.421 --> 19:51.691
We've got a visual on
the side street from our room.

19:51.724 --> 19:53.593
Carrion Falcon, you in position? Over.

19:57.196 --> 19:59.399
<i>Carrion Falcon,
are you in position? Over.</i>

19:59.432 --> 20:00.833
Roger that, Eagle Eye.

20:00.867 --> 20:04.203
In position and waiting
on your signal. Over.

20:04.237 --> 20:05.905
Over and out, I mean.

20:26.259 --> 20:28.394
<i>♪ Things to do ♪</i>

20:28.428 --> 20:33.266
<i>♪ Can't let my shoes Pick dust up ♪</i>

20:33.299 --> 20:35.268
<i>♪ Won't slow down ♪</i>

20:35.301 --> 20:39.539
<i>♪ I can't afford To let up... ♪</i>

20:39.572 --> 20:42.008
- Excuse me.
- Pardon me.

20:43.443 --> 20:44.644
Can I get another gin and tonic, please?

20:44.677 --> 20:45.878
Ah, yes.

20:45.912 --> 20:47.614
And the president
is very pleased

20:47.647 --> 20:49.315
with this conservative movement

20:49.349 --> 20:50.883
you got going out here with Reagan.

20:50.917 --> 20:53.987
John, we're not building it
for the president's pleasure.

20:54.020 --> 20:56.723
We consider this
our own movement out here,

20:56.756 --> 20:58.491
a-a new conservative politics

20:58.524 --> 21:01.561
centered around the Christian family,

21:01.594 --> 21:04.030
not making nice with Red China.

21:05.798 --> 21:07.934
All I'm saying
is that Ronnie's endorsement

21:07.967 --> 21:09.902
would mean the world to Dick.

21:09.936 --> 21:11.638
The only thing that means dick to Dick

21:11.671 --> 21:13.039
is more glory for Dick.

21:13.272 --> 21:15.441
Both of you, stop it.

21:15.475 --> 21:17.410
Don't tell me y'all
are still talking shop.

21:17.443 --> 21:18.845
Your husband here set a trap for me.

21:18.878 --> 21:20.913
I've been struggling to get out of it.

21:21.714 --> 21:22.949
I've been trying to wriggle my way

21:22.982 --> 21:24.651
out of his snare for 15 years.

21:28.021 --> 21:29.722
- Michael.
- Oh.

21:29.756 --> 21:31.591
Would you like to join me
in a game of pool?

21:31.624 --> 21:33.359
Maybe it'll make him jealous.

21:33.393 --> 21:34.661
I'd love nothing more.

21:42.535 --> 21:44.370
<i>Oh, God.</i>

21:44.404 --> 21:45.905
I forgot the first rule of billiards.

21:45.938 --> 21:47.040
Never put money on a game

21:47.073 --> 21:48.508
when there's a Southern woman involved.

21:48.541 --> 21:50.476
Mm.

21:50.510 --> 21:51.844
Now, tell me something.

21:53.079 --> 21:55.048
When Reagan went
for the nomination in '68,

21:55.081 --> 21:57.083
did he make a stop in Pine Bluff?

21:57.316 --> 21:59.585
Uh, I can't say that we did.

21:59.619 --> 22:01.387
Mm, it's probably for the best.

22:01.421 --> 22:03.656
They're just wild for Nixon down there.

22:03.690 --> 22:05.525
They love him even more than they love me.

22:07.994 --> 22:09.696
All right.

22:09.729 --> 22:11.998
One Mitchell gets me toast,
and the other one butters me up

22:12.031 --> 22:13.800
for the Reagan endorsement.
Is that how this works?

22:13.833 --> 22:15.935
<i>Oh, no, don't be ridiculous.</i>

22:15.968 --> 22:18.071
You're more than just
some jacket potato to us.

22:18.104 --> 22:19.605
You're a dear friend, Michael.

22:19.639 --> 22:21.374
Scotch, please.

22:21.407 --> 22:22.809
<i>Nixon's on the road
to reelection.</i>

22:22.842 --> 22:24.077
We all know that.

22:24.110 --> 22:26.479
But his reputation's taken a huge hit.

22:26.512 --> 22:29.382
<i>People know what he did to Musky,</i>

22:29.415 --> 22:32.051
what he and Kissinger did
to tank the peace talks in '68.

22:32.085 --> 22:33.886
That didn't play too well in California.

22:33.920 --> 22:36.389
Yeah, that was a tough call in '68.

22:37.623 --> 22:39.592
Not as tough as the one Ronnie had to make

22:39.625 --> 22:41.861
to book his flight home
after he lost the nomination.

22:41.894 --> 22:43.396
Beloved.

22:43.429 --> 22:45.798
In four years, Ronnie wants to run

22:45.832 --> 22:47.934
a presidential campaign that's based on--

22:47.967 --> 22:51.738
Yeah, on fair representation
and-and moral integrity

22:51.771 --> 22:54.440
and all bullshit, bullshit, bullshit.

22:55.608 --> 22:56.843
You know, with that attitude,
it's a wonder

22:56.876 --> 22:59.846
you haven't racked up our endorsement yet.

22:59.879 --> 23:01.848
Well, with that kind of blind confidence,

23:01.881 --> 23:03.015
it's a wonder you haven't been able

23:03.049 --> 23:04.617
to break through in the South.

23:05.952 --> 23:07.453
<i>You know, if I were Reagan, I would wonder</i>

23:07.487 --> 23:10.923
why someone as charming
and noble as myself

23:10.957 --> 23:12.658
could get crushed in the South

23:12.692 --> 23:14.994
by a supposed liar and cheat like Nixon.

23:15.027 --> 23:17.463
<i>It's no mystery,</i>

23:17.497 --> 23:19.165
at least not to the people of Pine Bluff.

23:19.398 --> 23:22.635
<i>They put their faith in Nixon,
and in return,</i>

23:22.668 --> 23:25.505
he won the presidency for them,
and now everything he does

23:25.538 --> 23:27.740
looks like a confirmation of their faith.

23:27.774 --> 23:30.543
<i>So what if he had to get down
in the mud to do it?</i>

23:30.576 --> 23:33.079
Even Christ had to wash a few dirty feet.

23:35.715 --> 23:37.183
Are you actually comparing Dick Nixon

23:37.416 --> 23:38.751
to Jesus Christ right now?

23:38.785 --> 23:40.186
No.

23:40.419 --> 23:42.922
Jesus Christ wouldn't make it
through the Republican primary.

23:52.865 --> 23:53.900
<i>...their Constitution</i>

23:53.933 --> 23:55.802
<i>and their love of apple pie.</i>

23:55.835 --> 23:57.904
<i>It is difficult to alert this country</i>

23:57.937 --> 23:59.572
<i>and throughout the media</i>

23:59.605 --> 24:02.008
<i>that the conspiracy
is not something small.</i>

24:02.041 --> 24:04.443
<i>It is huge, and it is beyond the realm</i>

24:04.477 --> 24:06.579
<i>of most people's imagination.</i>

24:06.612 --> 24:08.781
<i>The conspiracy is for the world domination</i>

24:08.815 --> 24:10.650
<i>of the United States.</i>

24:12.885 --> 24:14.654
Down by two in the fourth quarter,

24:14.687 --> 24:16.656
the young star from North Augusta

24:16.689 --> 24:19.525
lines up for a 48-yarder.

24:19.559 --> 24:21.928
I gotta tell you,
this is a risky one for Wills.

24:21.961 --> 24:25.164
A lot riding on this.
Can he pull this off?

24:26.732 --> 24:27.733
Ooh.

24:28.734 --> 24:29.802
Sorry, sir.

24:31.037 --> 24:32.572
Oh, man.

24:38.177 --> 24:39.178
Oh, shoot.

25:00.700 --> 25:03.069
Eagle Eye, the final gophers
have left the hole.

25:03.102 --> 25:05.538
Repeat, we are a go on the hole.

26:03.629 --> 26:04.864
<i>Ah, coño.</i>

26:52.979 --> 26:53.946
Shit.

26:53.980 --> 26:56.182
- What?
- Quiet.

26:56.215 --> 26:59.118
The transceivers, they're back at HQ.

26:59.151 --> 27:00.619
Liddy wanted fresh batteries.

27:00.653 --> 27:02.355
I told him the batteries
were already fresh.

27:02.388 --> 27:04.323
- Fuck me!
- Quiet!

27:08.160 --> 27:12.098
Eagle Eye, this is Carrion Falcon.

27:12.131 --> 27:13.733
We are earless.

27:13.766 --> 27:17.970
Repeat, we are without ears. Over.

27:18.004 --> 27:19.872
Cleared to retrieve. Over.

27:19.905 --> 27:21.941
But make it quick. Over.

27:21.974 --> 27:23.409
Oh, shit, get out of here.

27:23.642 --> 27:25.711
Shit, shit, shit, shit,

27:25.745 --> 27:28.714
shit, shit, shit, shit, shit, shit.

27:28.748 --> 27:30.883
Shit, shit,

27:30.916 --> 27:33.652
shit, shit, shit, shit.

27:33.686 --> 27:36.255
Shit, shit, shit, shit.

27:36.288 --> 27:39.158
Watch it, asshole!

27:39.191 --> 27:40.826
Shit, shit, shit, shit, shit.

28:08.387 --> 28:09.889
Hey, man.

28:09.922 --> 28:12.892
Hey, you can't be putting tape
on the door like this.

28:12.925 --> 28:14.894
It's against code or something.

28:14.927 --> 28:17.763
Pardon me, sir?
Hawkins Deli is already closed.

28:17.797 --> 28:19.698
Do you know if there's another place open?

28:19.732 --> 28:21.767
Sorry, man,
it's my first night on the job.

28:23.369 --> 28:25.771
- All right, thanks anyway.
- Mm-hmm.

28:27.740 --> 28:30.076
Hey, wait up.

28:30.109 --> 28:31.277
Um...

28:33.045 --> 28:34.814
...I just remembered
there's a burger joint

28:34.847 --> 28:35.981
down the street from here.

28:36.015 --> 28:36.982
Come on, I'll take you to it.

28:39.718 --> 28:41.954
Like the wind, man, go!

28:47.159 --> 28:50.863
You can always put on
another jacket, but, like,

28:50.896 --> 28:53.432
if it's hot, you can only
take off so many layers, so...

28:53.466 --> 28:55.468
Yeah, well, I mean, but see,
in Atlanta, you can...

28:55.501 --> 28:58.404
Shit, shit, shit.

29:23.529 --> 29:26.398
Clay Pigeon, this is Carrion Falcon.

29:26.432 --> 29:29.034
Something's wrong with the door down here.

29:29.068 --> 29:31.904
Requesting immediate assistance. Over.

29:33.873 --> 29:35.774
Help me. Over.

29:35.808 --> 29:37.209
What the fuck?

29:38.777 --> 29:39.912
Something's wrong with the fucking door.

29:39.945 --> 29:41.347
Get Road Runner down there immediately.

29:41.380 --> 29:42.915
Copy.

29:42.948 --> 29:44.250
Road Runner is on his way.

29:44.283 --> 29:46.919
I repeat, Road Runner's on his way. Over.

29:51.090 --> 29:52.491
All right,
let me do a patty melt,

29:52.525 --> 29:54.860
add Swiss cheese, and let me
get some extra mushrooms.

29:54.894 --> 29:56.829
Sorry, buddy, ran out of mushrooms.

29:57.563 --> 29:59.064
Y'all ran outta mushrooms?

29:59.098 --> 30:00.432
Look, pal, it's a mushroom town.

30:00.466 --> 30:02.034
What can I tell you?

30:06.906 --> 30:09.108
<i>Venga, cabrón. Vamos.</i>

30:23.389 --> 30:24.557
Oh, whoa.

30:26.225 --> 30:27.426
Venga.

30:27.459 --> 30:29.428
My strength is leaving me.

30:29.461 --> 30:30.529
<i>Rápido, rápido.</i>

30:32.565 --> 30:33.866
Copy.

30:44.376 --> 30:45.411
What the hell?

30:45.444 --> 30:47.479
The lock's all worn to shit.

30:47.513 --> 30:49.215
Gonzalez figured this'd be easier.

30:51.116 --> 30:52.618
Okay, okay, okay, okay.

30:53.319 --> 30:55.588
<i>Venga. Rápido, rápido.</i>

30:55.621 --> 30:56.989
<i>Vamos.</i>

30:57.957 --> 31:00.426
- Take it easy.
- Put it back on.

31:19.912 --> 31:20.946
Yeah, well, you have a good night.

31:20.980 --> 31:22.414
- Yeah, you too, man.
