It's Rilke.

32:30.049 --> 32:31.950
Yes, we had books in Queens too.

32:34.453 --> 32:35.954
John Newton Mitchell, I didn't know

32:35.988 --> 32:38.223
you were a such romantic.

32:38.257 --> 32:40.225
How do you know I'm not
just trying to get inside

32:40.259 --> 32:44.096
those Pine Bluff panties,
my little jacket potato?

32:46.198 --> 32:47.700
What's your angle here?

32:50.369 --> 32:52.271
I was thinking about
what we were talking about

32:52.304 --> 32:53.405
on the plane.

32:55.007 --> 32:56.508
About holding on to a good thing.

32:58.110 --> 32:59.745
And this is a good thing.

33:03.115 --> 33:05.517
I like what they're doing
out here for Reagan.

33:07.252 --> 33:09.722
And I was thinking that...

33:09.755 --> 33:12.191
after the campaign,

33:12.224 --> 33:15.327
maybe there'd be a place for us
out here in California.

33:16.695 --> 33:18.230
You want to move across the country

33:18.263 --> 33:19.465
and work for Reagan?

33:23.068 --> 33:25.070
The two of us are unstoppable.

33:26.271 --> 33:28.574
But I was never the one
driving that train.

33:31.076 --> 33:32.311
It was always you.

33:34.480 --> 33:38.217
Lord, look who sounds drunk now.

33:38.250 --> 33:40.219
Come here, let me sober you up.

33:45.691 --> 33:48.560
- Poetry.
- Mm.

33:59.171 --> 34:01.273
<i>Sparrow, come in.</i>

34:01.306 --> 34:03.275
<i>Looks like someone
just pulled up out front.</i>

34:03.308 --> 34:05.677
<i>Can you make them out
from your vantage? Over.</i>

34:13.719 --> 34:16.722
Just some hippies, sir.
Nothing to worry about. Over.

34:44.550 --> 34:47.119
<i>What's your status,
Carrion Falcon? Over.</i>

34:49.188 --> 34:51.256
Wrapping up in here. Over.

34:55.327 --> 34:56.695
Hey, guys, building's closed.
You can't come in here.

34:56.728 --> 34:58.263
You're the one who
called the cops, aren't you?

34:58.297 --> 34:59.364
Yeah, I mean--

34:59.398 --> 35:01.500
Relax, Mr. Tibbs.

35:01.533 --> 35:03.368
We were on vice detail
when we got the call.

35:04.503 --> 35:05.838
Maybe tell us what the hell's going on

35:05.871 --> 35:07.473
so we can get back to it.

35:07.506 --> 35:09.274
Okay, uh, I found a piece of tape

35:09.308 --> 35:12.144
on the parking garage door.

35:12.177 --> 35:13.846
- Tape?
- Over the door latch,

35:13.879 --> 35:15.581
like somebody was keeping it open.

35:15.614 --> 35:17.149
I thought it was a mistake the first time,

35:17.182 --> 35:18.350
and then it happened again,

35:18.383 --> 35:20.652
and I found another piece
on the sixth floor.

35:20.686 --> 35:23.455
- Hmm.
- Okay, uh, not to worry.

35:23.489 --> 35:25.290
We'll take it from here.

35:29.194 --> 35:31.129
Oh, um, you guys gonna head up there now?

35:31.163 --> 35:33.699
I can come with you, you know,
be your backup if you need.

35:33.732 --> 35:35.234
Uh, that's all right. We're good.

35:35.267 --> 35:37.336
Uh, you stay down here and, uh--

35:37.369 --> 35:38.470
Watch our perimeter.

35:38.504 --> 35:41.807
That's right, watch our six, Officer.

36:13.438 --> 36:14.773
Walkies off.

36:26.518 --> 36:29.321
Hide, hide. <i>Andale, andale.</i>

36:56.949 --> 36:58.550
Eagle Eye, were any of our guys

36:58.584 --> 37:00.686
by chance wearing a sport coat? Over.

37:01.987 --> 37:04.356
Our men are in suits.

37:04.389 --> 37:07.593
Did you mean suit jacket, Sparrow? Over.

37:07.626 --> 37:09.394
Maybe it's a windbreaker.

37:11.430 --> 37:13.599
What is a windbreaker again? Over.

37:15.300 --> 37:16.935
A windbreaker is the lighter version

37:16.969 --> 37:19.237
of what we typically refer to
as a jacket. Over.

37:19.271 --> 37:21.540
<i>I thought
that was a parka. Over.</i>

37:21.573 --> 37:23.475
No, no, no, a parka is a--

37:23.508 --> 37:24.910
it's-it's a whole different thing.

37:24.943 --> 37:27.879
It's much longer,
like a-a trench coat or a...

37:27.913 --> 37:28.981
- Yeah, it's a duster.
- Duster.

37:29.014 --> 37:30.716
<i>Think, uh, Gary Cooper in</i> Shane.

37:30.749 --> 37:31.883
<i>Over.</i>

37:31.917 --> 37:32.985
Duster.

38:04.683 --> 38:06.718
Mother of shit.

38:06.752 --> 38:08.720
Eagle Eye, the hippies are armed.

38:08.754 --> 38:10.689
The fucking hippies are armed.

38:10.722 --> 38:12.824
Wait, wait, wait. What's that, Sparrow?

38:12.858 --> 38:14.493
Armed pursuants on the sixth floor.

38:14.526 --> 38:15.794
They're headed for the gopher hole.

38:15.827 --> 38:17.596
Mayday! Mayday!

38:17.629 --> 38:18.930
Ah, ah!

38:18.964 --> 38:20.866
Carrion Falcon, did you hear that?

38:20.899 --> 38:22.634
<i>You got company on your six.
Abort mission.</i>

38:22.668 --> 38:25.470
I repeat, abort mission.
Please acknowledge. Over.

38:25.504 --> 38:26.672
Fuck, their walkies must be off.

38:26.705 --> 38:27.939
What's happening over there?

38:27.973 --> 38:29.608
How the fuck did you miss those guys?

38:29.641 --> 38:31.443
It was a goddamn hippie in a sport coat.

38:31.476 --> 38:33.311
- What was I supposed to do?
- You said windbreaker.

38:33.345 --> 38:34.646
Hippies don't wear windbreakers.

38:34.680 --> 38:35.580
Doesn't fucking matter!

38:35.614 --> 38:37.082
I'm gonna pack up my shit.

38:37.315 --> 38:38.583
- I'll meet you in the lobby.
- Get the fucking shit out now.

38:38.617 --> 38:39.818
Grab the equipment.

38:39.851 --> 38:41.586
Swear to God, how do you
fucking miss that shit?

38:57.402 --> 38:59.471
- Fucking God damn it.
- Damn it.

38:59.504 --> 39:01.707
Help him. Help him. Get--

39:01.740 --> 39:03.108
Don't leave any fucking papers.

39:03.341 --> 39:06.812
I got no fucking fingernails. God.

39:09.081 --> 39:10.615
<i>Jump in.</i>

39:59.798 --> 40:02.834
All right,
we know you're in here.

40:05.470 --> 40:07.606
You, get up. Stand up.

40:07.639 --> 40:11.576
Let me see your hands.
Slowly, slowly, slowly.

40:11.610 --> 40:12.844
Don't shoot.

40:17.015 --> 40:18.583
Don't shoot.

40:24.055 --> 40:25.891
Are you guys cops?

40:25.924 --> 40:27.859
What the fuck does it look like?

40:29.494 --> 40:31.563
May I see your badge?

40:46.511 --> 40:48.180
You're horrible.

40:50.916 --> 40:53.018
Oh, God, I'm trying to get to the bench.

40:53.051 --> 40:54.686
Oh, ooh!

40:56.822 --> 40:58.890
- Sir.
- Oh, heavens.

40:58.924 --> 41:00.892
Sorry to bother you.

41:00.926 --> 41:03.929
There's a phone call for you.
It's-it's Mr. Dean.

41:03.962 --> 41:05.697
- He says it's urgent.
- Patch him through.

41:10.235 --> 41:12.938
I don't like the new bodyguard.

41:12.971 --> 41:14.906
Well, you never
like the new bodyguard.

41:18.109 --> 41:19.678
I had a good time tonight.

41:19.711 --> 41:21.580
Me too.

41:23.915 --> 41:26.585
All right, take your call.
I'll go check on Marty.

41:58.250 --> 42:00.118
Somebody's playing possum.

42:06.091 --> 42:07.525
You seem happy.

42:07.559 --> 42:08.994
I am happy.

42:13.965 --> 42:16.234
Daddy bought it for me
at the airport.

42:16.268 --> 42:18.303
People say it's scary.

42:18.536 --> 42:21.139
- It's pretty boring so far.
- Hmm.

42:21.172 --> 42:23.675
Well, let me know how it turns out.

42:25.043 --> 42:26.711
She snores.

42:50.235 --> 42:51.269
Mitchell.

42:51.303 --> 42:53.204
Hello, sir.

42:53.238 --> 42:55.807
I'm-I'm sorry to disturb you on vacation.

42:55.840 --> 42:58.310
How is it down there? Or up there?

42:58.343 --> 43:00.845
Where is California
in relation to the Philippines

43:00.879 --> 43:02.981
latitude-wise? I don't know.

43:03.014 --> 43:06.584
It's just, I've had some
disturbing news from Jeb, sir.

43:06.618 --> 43:08.320
For Christ, fuck.

43:08.353 --> 43:12.090
It seems there was
a mix-up at the Watergate.

43:12.123 --> 43:16.594
A security guard, uh, bust
the whole operation, Jeb says.

43:16.628 --> 43:17.929
Bust it wide open.

43:17.963 --> 43:22.334
Apparently, a-a-a door
was-was taped incorrectly.

43:22.367 --> 43:23.935
What the fuck are you talking about?

43:23.969 --> 43:26.638
It was-it was difficult to
make out the details exactly.

43:26.671 --> 43:29.708
Jeb was crying when he told me.
He was actually crying, sir.

43:29.741 --> 43:32.677
- Fucking Christ on the cross.
- <i>I'm sorry, sir.</i>

43:32.711 --> 43:34.679
This is the first
I'm hearing about all this.

43:35.947 --> 43:39.651
- Was Liddy arrested too?
- Well, no, uh, Liddy got away,

43:39.684 --> 43:41.920
Jeb says, as did Hunt and Baldwin.

43:41.953 --> 43:44.322
Thank the shit Christ.

43:45.190 --> 43:47.625
So there's no direct ties to the campaign.

43:47.659 --> 43:49.894
Well-well, here's the thing, sir.

43:49.928 --> 43:53.131
Uh, McCord did not get away.

43:56.034 --> 43:58.403
Liddy let McCord go in there?

43:58.636 --> 43:59.971
Yes, sir.

44:00.005 --> 44:03.208
I specifically said
I want no one with ties

44:03.241 --> 44:04.976
to the campaign on-site.

44:05.010 --> 44:08.413
Well, apparently we're short on Cubans.

44:08.646 --> 44:10.982
<i>All right, get
the fuck back to D.C. tonight.</i>

44:11.016 --> 44:12.984
<i>You hear me?</i>

44:13.018 --> 44:15.086
The next 48 hours
are gonna be crucial.

44:15.120 --> 44:18.790
We'll have to go low and slow.
Let's not make any big moves.

44:18.823 --> 44:20.091
I-I understand, sir.

44:20.125 --> 44:21.893
Only I was hoping to stop in LA.

44:21.926 --> 44:23.928
We'll regroup the whole team
when we get in.

44:23.962 --> 44:25.930
I'll get Jeb to write up a containment.

44:26.798 --> 44:29.300
Sir, uh, before you go, sir,

44:29.334 --> 44:31.736
uh, one more thing.

44:31.770 --> 44:33.071
I- I don't know how to put this.

44:33.104 --> 44:37.008
Uh, Jeb and I were wondering
about your wife.

44:39.677 --> 44:41.279
What about her?

44:41.312 --> 44:42.414
<i>Well, you know,
I'd- I'd never go</i>

44:42.447 --> 44:43.948
<i>on the record with this, sir,</i>

44:43.982 --> 44:46.785
but McCord did work in your home.

44:46.818 --> 44:48.987
You really think that
when Martha sees his face

44:49.020 --> 44:50.989
in the newspaper, she won't call

44:51.022 --> 44:52.690
one of her journalist friends?

44:52.724 --> 44:53.958
<i>You said it yourself, sir,</i>

44:53.992 --> 44:56.461
<i>the next 48 hours are gonna be crucial.</i>

44:56.694 --> 44:58.329
Listen, Dean, I know you're trying to be

44:58.363 --> 45:00.265
a good little farmhand,
but you're gonna have to get

45:00.298 --> 45:02.901
your dick out of
the butter churn on this one.

45:04.736 --> 45:06.037
<i>You got it?</i>

45:06.071 --> 45:08.907
Yes-yes, sir.

45:08.940 --> 45:10.108
Won't happen again, sir.

45:21.486 --> 45:22.987
What's going on?

45:25.790 --> 45:28.126
You gotta promise you'll tell no one.

45:32.163 --> 45:33.364
I promise.

45:36.835 --> 45:38.837
Dean got himself caught up

45:38.870 --> 45:41.139
in a raid on a Filipino brothel.

45:41.172 --> 45:44.042
He's being forced out of the country.

45:44.075 --> 45:46.211
- You're kidding.
- You didn't hear it from me.

45:48.146 --> 45:51.316
I knew he was an operator
the moment I laid eyes on him.

45:53.084 --> 45:55.253
Oh, his sweet little girlfriend.

45:55.286 --> 45:56.454
She'll be mortified.

45:57.288 --> 45:59.023
Hmm.

45:59.057 --> 46:00.525
This is what happens when there's no trust

46:00.758 --> 46:02.327
between two people.

46:12.203 --> 46:13.838
Now, where were we?

46:15.840 --> 46:18.476
- Oh, yeah.
- Follow me.

46:24.816 --> 46:26.417
Well, well, well,

46:26.451 --> 46:28.553
Mr. Eye For Detail.

46:31.289 --> 46:33.124
You really saved the day here.

46:33.158 --> 46:34.859
Well, I'm just glad
I could represent myself

46:34.893 --> 46:36.528
on behalf of the building.

46:36.561 --> 46:41.432
The big bosses, uh,
have approved a small token

46:41.466 --> 46:44.836
of their appreciation
for your heroic actions

46:44.869 --> 46:46.471
during the course of the break-in.

46:56.915 --> 46:59.417
- What's this?
- <i>It's a raise.</i>

47:01.886 --> 47:03.254
Two fifty?

47:04.222 --> 47:05.323
Every week.

47:12.363 --> 47:13.865
I appreciate it.

47:34.118 --> 47:35.253
Mitchell?

48:13.091 --> 48:16.427
Honeybun? Where are you?

48:16.461 --> 48:18.096
Mitchell?

48:19.197 --> 48:20.898
Marty?

48:20.932 --> 48:22.300
Oh, Jesus.

48:22.333 --> 48:25.336
Oh, Peter, you scared me.

48:27.405 --> 48:29.507
Sorry, ma'am, I was just
getting some breakfast.

48:31.442 --> 48:33.311
Where is everyone?

48:33.344 --> 48:35.947
Oh, your daughter went
to Disneyland with Katarina.

48:36.981 --> 48:38.349
Yes, of course.

48:38.383 --> 48:39.684
And my husband?

48:39.917 --> 48:41.386
Mr. Mitchell had to fly to Washington

48:41.419 --> 48:42.987
for an urgent business meeting.

48:43.021 --> 48:45.089
His instructions
were to have you stay here.

48:46.557 --> 48:47.659
Oh.

48:52.163 --> 48:53.464
I think I'll just, uh...

48:55.233 --> 48:56.234
...give his office a call,

48:56.267 --> 48:57.568
make sure everything's all right.

49:00.038 --> 49:01.939
All right, Peter, seriously,
what is going on?

49:01.973 --> 49:03.041
Where is everyone?

49:03.074 --> 49:04.609
As I said, your husband
had an urgent meeting--

49:04.642 --> 49:07.945
Okay, well, stop saying that
and just tell me.

49:07.979 --> 49:10.348
Okay, there's no need to get hysterical.

49:10.381 --> 49:13.017
Why don't you just go back
to your room and relax?

49:14.619 --> 49:16.654
This is ridiculous.
I am calling my husband.

49:19.057 --> 49:20.425
You are not in charge here.

49:20.458 --> 49:22.126
- Do you understand me?
- Mm-hmm.

49:23.528 --> 49:25.396
Good.

49:25.430 --> 49:28.032
Your husband's a very busy man,

49:28.066 --> 49:30.468
and he doesn't have time
right now to take your call.

49:30.501 --> 49:31.969
Okay.

49:38.009 --> 49:39.210
Here.

49:40.745 --> 49:42.046
A little light reading.

49:48.186 --> 49:49.487
Good girl.

50:10.775 --> 50:12.243
To your right.

50:16.013 --> 50:17.315
To your left.

50:45.576 --> 50:47.545
<i>I'm sorry, sir.
Your party's not answering.</i>

50:47.578 --> 50:49.247
<i>Would you like to try another number?</i>

50:57.088 --> 50:58.689
So am I your date tonight?

51:00.458 --> 51:03.795
Okay, Sandra, you are my date

51:03.828 --> 51:07.532
to the Mormon Tabernacle Choir.

51:33.191 --> 51:35.259
<i>Should be the last of it.</i>

51:39.697 --> 51:41.599
I saw this in a dream, Howard.

51:43.868 --> 51:47.305
These flames consuming
our best-laid plans.

51:49.273 --> 51:50.641
It's all our fault.

51:52.477 --> 51:54.645
We made too many mistakes,

51:54.679 --> 51:56.314
too many assumptions.

52:00.718 --> 52:03.688
<i>The tide of our ideals</i>

52:03.721 --> 52:07.158
<i>dashed against reality's rocky shore.</i>

52:08.326 --> 52:10.695
<i>How could we have been so foolish</i>

52:10.728 --> 52:12.830
<i>as to not see it coming?</i>

52:12.864 --> 52:14.832
See what coming, Gordon?

52:18.436 --> 52:19.737
Retribution.
